<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-04-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-04-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="150" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d150">
                        <head>No. 15.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to General <persName type="to">Schenck</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-04-02"><hi rend="italic">April</hi> 2,
                                1872</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>We understand the British Government is bound to file Counter-Case, and
                            that their so doing will not prejudice any position they have taken, nor
                            affect any position of this Government. The rights of both parties will
                            be the same after filing as before.</p>
                        <p>Is the inquiry made at their request?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>FISH.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>